    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "ASTM F1717 compression-bending operating envelope for 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screw",
      "description": "Axial compressive load range: 0–2500 N applied at a crosshead displacement rate of 5 mm/min (±0.25 mm/min). Construct geometry: screw outer diameter 7.3–7.7 mm (nominal 7.5 mm), screw length 40–45 mm, rod diameter 5.5 mm (tolerance ±0.05 mm), interbody spacer height 26 mm (±0.5 mm). Test temperature: 23 ± 2 °C in ambient air. Displacement range evaluated: 0–40 mm. Cortical bone analog (UHMWPE block) density: 0.94–0.96 g/cm³. Coverage gaps: single load rate tested; titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) only; no cyclic or fatigue loading in this COU."
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Applicability constraint: non-cannulated Ti-6Al-4V 7.5 mm screw, static monotonic loading only",
      "description": "Model predictions are applicable only to non-cannulated pedicle screws manufactured from Ti-6Al-4V ELI with outer diameter 7.3–7.7 mm and length 40–45 mm, tested under static monotonic ASTM F1717 compression-bending at room temperature (21–25 °C). Extrapolation to cannulated designs, stainless steel alloys, dynamic/fatigue loading regimes, or screw diameters outside the 7.3–7.7 mm band is explicitly out of scope and requires separate V&V activities."
    }
  },
  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/sensitivity/fea-material-geometry-sa",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Material property and geometry sensitivity analysis for pedicle screw FEA",
    "description": "One-at-a-time and Morris screening sensitivity analyses were performed varying Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (±5%), yield strength (±8%), screw outer diameter (±0.2 mm), and bone analog elastic modulus (±10%). Construct stiffness QoI showed greatest sensitivity to screw outer diameter (normalized sensitivity index 0.38) and bone analog modulus (0.29); yield force was most sensitive to Ti-6Al-4V yield strength (0.44). All parameter perturbations produced QoI changes within ±7%, remaining inside the 10% acceptance bound and confirming that the dominant uncertainty sources are bounded by material certification tolerances."
  },
